article.description: — Bernardo Da Silva had 14 points off the bench to lift Hawaii to a 62-50 win over Cal State Bakersfield on Saturday night.
article.headline: Da Silva carries Hawaii past CS Bakersfield 62-50
article.linkText: Da Silva carries Hawaii past CS Bakersfield 62-50
article.story: HONOLULU -- — Bernardo Da Silva had 14 points off the bench to lift Hawaii to a 62-50 win over Cal State Bakersfield on Saturday night. JoVon McClanahan had 11 points and six assists for Hawaii (15-9, 11-4 Big West Conference). Junior Madut added 10 points. Cal State Bakersfield totaled 20 points in the second half, a season low for the team. Shawn Stith had 12 points for the Roadrunners (7-16, 2-12). Justin Edler-Davis added eight rebounds. The Rainbow Warriors also defeated Cal State Bakersfield 63-59 on Jan. 20. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
